Reasoning: The paper discusses the formalization and comparison of metrics for tree graphs, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), as the paper deals with the study of relations between biological entities and the formalization of multiple distances to compare tree graphs. The second most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper discusses the discriminatory power of the metrics and their time complexity. The third most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper discusses the time complexity of computing the metrics and presents a new way to represent tree graphs. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry), as the paper deals with the study of graphs and their properties. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.BIO (Computational Biology), as the paper discusses the study of relations between biological entities.
